   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1870_09_27_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Consulat_des_Norddeutschen_Bundes_Westphal_Nagasaki_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>Consulate of the North German Confederation <lb/>Nagasaki, 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> September 1870.<lb/>Upon request of the Japanese government,<lb/>Police
                Authority, I am making you aware<lb/>that as per the regulations in force
                here<lb/>shooting is prohibited in the Foreign<lb/>Settlement.<lb/>The said
                authority is therefore demanding your<lb/>punishment for disregarding this
                proscription on<lb/>the night of the 22nd of the current month and <lb/>although I
                have persuaded them to withdraw <lb/>the mentioned application partially this time,
                <lb/>I am informing you, however, that any further<lb/>such transgression will
                result in the prescribed <lb/>punishment. <lb/>Consulate administrator <lb/>Georg
                Westphal<lb/>To <lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler + Co.<lb/>Nagasaki</p>
         <pb facs="1870_09_27_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Consulat_des_Norddeutschen_Bundes_Westphal_Nagasaki_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <pb facs="1870_09_27_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Consulat_des_Norddeutschen_Bundes_Westphal_Nagasaki_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1870_09_27_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Consulat_des_Norddeutschen_Bundes_Westphal_Nagasaki_4.tif" n="4"/>
         <p>⟨1870<lb/>G. Westphal<lb/>27th Sep.⟩</p>
      </body>
